cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with segmentation in 3-D scans using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of bidirectional convolutional long short-term memory and time-distributed wrappers suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses memory restrictions, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
